msContents.summary: Commentary on Aristotle, in two parts.

supportDesc.extent: 470 leaves : 227 x 161 (160 x 113) mm. bound to 232 x 172 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i (contemporary paper) + 453 + i (contemporary paper); [vii, 1-446]; modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto. Contemporary numeration in ink, 16-70, every eighth folio (in a few cases, every sixth), upper outer corner.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by a single hand.

decoDesc.decoNote: Illustrated with three engraved plates: a frontispiece depicting 10 philosophers, Plato, Thomas [Aquinas], Aristotle, Pythagoras, Seneca, Epicurus, Socrates, Diogenes, Porphyrus, Erasmus, the signature on this plate is difficult to read, "Chez...a la Ville d'Anders"; engraved title page with architectural cartouche [left blank], signed Rabel, avec priuilege du Roy; and a framed allegorical female figure, "La Logique," plate unsigned. The plate of "La Logique" has an almost identical match in Ms. Codex 883.

origin.p: Written in France[?] in the 17th century.

history.provenance: Formerly part of Librairie Jean Clavreuil (bookplate, inside upper cover).
